<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-30T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="498" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>Telegram 3653, August 23, to London, <ref target="#pg_1055">page
                                    1055</ref>, set forth the tentative views of the Department of
                                State regarding a delay in the resumption of reparations deliveries.
                                General <persName corresp="#p_CLD1">Clay</persName>’s comments were
                                sent in telegram 72088, August 25, from London, <ref target="#pg_1059">page 1059</ref>.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>